First Lady Michelle Obama delivered a speech at the United States Military Academy Graduation Family Banquet in 2011. She expressed her gratitude for being invited and praised the cadets for their dedication and the values they embody. She acknowledged the challenges they faced during their time at West Point but also highlighted their achievements, both academically and athletically. Obama emphasized the importance of family and the role it plays in supporting military personnel. She spoke about the sacrifices military families make and the need for the country to recognize and support them. She mentioned the Joining Forces campaign, which aimed to unite various sectors in supporting military families. Obama concluded by encouraging the graduates to remember the importance of family and to serve their country with honor.